          "               + ForexRate = client rate.\r\n",
          "*Percentage Change Calculation Rules:\r\n",
          "When calculating average daily volume across a date range for a segment (Region, Regulation, or Region+Regulation), never use AVG() directly on rows. Rows in the base table may span multiple sub-dimensions (e.g., multiple Regulations within a Region), so AVG() would average per-row values instead of daily totals.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Instead, always compute the daily average as: SUM(Volume) / COUNT(DISTINCT Date) — this first totals all volume per day at the segment level, then divides by the number of active days.\r\n",
